The Democratic Alliance says it will be laying formal complaints with Parliament's Ethics Committee. This in relation to the ANC's plans to appoint what the DA calls a rogues gallery of people to certain committee chair positions in Parliament. Courtesy #DStv403 PARLIAMENT - The DA will challenge the appointment of controversial ANC nominees to Parliament's portfolio committees on Tuesday. READ: Frolick elected Parliament's chair of chairs The official opposition says those linked to state capture can't be allowed to head these committees. Included in the list are former Zuma-era ministers Faith Muthambi, Bongani Bongo and Mosebenzi Zwane. READ: Mazzone slams ANC chairpersons Former energy minister Tina Joemat-Pettersson is also expected to face competition, as is former North West premier Supra Mahumapelo. The DA says they don't have a track record of good governance.